TCommandMediator.ExecuteCmd(ICommand) Method

Namespace: Emetra.Command.Mediator
Syntax
Delphi
public
 function ExecuteCmd( const ACommand: ICommand ): boolean; overload;

Parameters

ACommand
Type: ICommand

The command to pass on to a RegisterAsCommandReceiver handler.

Return Value

Type: boolean

The return value indicates whether this command was successfully executed. The definition of success is the responsibility of the RegisterAsCommandReceiver handler.

Implements

ICommandReceiver.ExecuteCmd(ICommand)
Remarks

Exceptions thrown in the handler may or may not be handled there. If an error occurs and the method returns false, it is normally the handler's responsibility to take necessary steps to log the failed attempt. The client that issued the command may also do so.
